Package uk.blankaspect.common.basictree

This package contains an abstract base class and concrete subclasses that implement a node that represents a null value, nodes that contain instances of fundamental Java types (boolean, int, long, double and String), and nodes that contain other nodes (a list and a map).

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractNode
    This is the abstract base class of a node of a tree.
    BooleanNode
    This class implements a node that contains a Boolean value.
    DoubleNode
    This class implements a node that contains a double-precision floating-point number.
    IntNode
    This class implements a node that contains an integer.
    ListNode
    This class implements a node that contains a sequence of elements that are nodes.
    LongNode
    This class implements a node that contains a long integer.
    MapNode
    This class implements a node that contains a collection of key–value pairs whose keys are strings and whose values are nodes.
    MapNode.Pair
    This class encapsulates a key–value pair of a map node.

Package uk.blankaspect.common.basictree Description

This package contains an abstract base class and concrete subclasses that implement
  • a node that represents a null value,
  • nodes that contain instances of fundamental Java types (boolean, int, long, double and String), and
  • nodes that contain other nodes (a list and a map).

This package depends on the following packages:

  • uk.blankaspect.common.tree
